Kuttipuram Sub-Inspector Aravindan said Karandlajeâ€™s allegations were not true.

Speaking to Indianexpress.com, he said, â€œWe looked into it. What she (Sobha Karandlaje) has alleged is not true. The people in Cherukunnu colony would get water from a borewell as part of a drinking water project of the panchayat. However, the motor was burnt, so water couldnâ€™t be supplied through it for the past one year. Another borewell was installed in the house of a Muslim family, from which the locals had been taking water. That borewell was originally supplied by the Krishi Bhavan through the KSEB, and was to be used strictly for irrigation purposes. So when KSEB opposed supply of water for other uses, the family stopped it.â€

Aravindan said for the past two days, Seva Bharathi of the RSS had been providing water to the locals.

â€œThis is what has happened. The episode has no connection to the CAA protests. Following the incident, the district collector, panchayat president and the taluk officer visited the spot and promised to arrange funds to get the old borewell functioning again,â€ the Sub-Inspector added.

Aravindan said he will proceed with the case against the BJP MP by collecting more evidence and eyewitness accounts.

